    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-low heat with the <strong>cornfloured cheese</strong>, <strong>soft cheese</strong> and 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong></p><p>Cook for 3 min or until melted and thickened</p><p>Once thickened, add your <strong>wholegrain mustard </strong>(not a fan of mustard? Just add a little!), <strong>Henderson's Relish</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong>, then remove the pan from the heat – this is your <strong>rarebit sauce</strong></p>",
